{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":509,"text":"People say things about religion all the time."},{"time":4736,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":6710,"text":"The late, great Christopher Hitchens"},{"time":8960,"text":"wrote a book called \"God Is Not Great\""},{"time":10381,"text":"whose subtitle was, \"Religion Poisons Everything.\""},{"time":13913,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":15286,"text":"But last month, in Time magazine,"},{"time":19380,"text":"Rabbi David Wolpe, who I gather\nis referred to as America's rabbi,"},{"time":23393,"text":"said, to balance that against\nthat negative characterization,"},{"time":28031,"text":"that no important form of social change"},{"time":30655,"text":"can be brought about except through organized religion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34995,"text":"Now, remarks of this sort on the negative"},{"time":36973,"text":"and the positive side are very old."},{"time":40010,"text":"I have one in my pocket here"},{"time":42451,"text":"from the first century BCE by Lucretius,"},{"time":48366,"text":"the author of \"On the Nature of Things,\" who said,"},{"time":51229,"text":"\"Tantum religio potuit suadere malorum\" --"},{"time":55512,"text":"I should have been able to learn that by heart â€”"},{"time":58134,"text":"which is, that's how much religion"},{"time":60822,"text":"is able to persuade people to do evil,"},{"time":63332,"text":"and he was talking about the fact"},{"time":65119,"text":"of Agamemnon's decision to place his daughter"},{"time":68164,"text":"Iphigenia on an altar of sacrifice"},{"time":70075,"text":"in order to preserve the prospects of his army."},{"time":73575,"text":"So there have been these long debates"},{"time":76471,"text":"over the centuries, in that case, actually,"},{"time":78360,"text":"we can say over the millennia, about religion."},{"time":79946,"text":"People have talked about it a lot,"},{"time":81799,"text":"and they've said good and bad"},{"time":83597,"text":"and indifferent things about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87106,"text":"What I want to persuade you of today"},{"time":88841,"text":"is of a very simple claim,"},{"time":90444,"text":"which is that these debates are"},{"time":92681,"text":"in a certain sense preposterous,"},{"time":95174,"text":"because there is no such thing as religion"},{"time":99345,"text":"about which to make these claims."},{"time":101080,"text":"There isn't a thing called religion,"},{"time":102468,"text":"and so it can't be good or bad."},{"time":105519,"text":"It can't even be indifferent."},{"time":107680,"text":"And if you think about claims"},{"time":110139,"text":"about the nonexistence of things,"},{"time":114127,"text":"one obvious way to try and establish"},{"time":116319,"text":"the nonexistence of a purported thing"},{"time":118771,"text":"would be to offer a definition of that thing"},{"time":121229,"text":"and then to see whether anything satisfied it."},{"time":123990,"text":"I'm going to start out on that little route"},{"time":127202,"text":"to begin with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128411,"text":"So if you look in the dictionaries"},{"time":130988,"text":"and if you think about it,"},{"time":132138,"text":"one very natural definition of religion"},{"time":134507,"text":"is that it involves belief in gods or in spiritual beings."},{"time":140324,"text":"As I say, this is in many dictionaries,"},{"time":141830,"text":"but you'll also find it actually"},{"time":144581,"text":"in the work of Sir Edward Tylor,"},{"time":146208,"text":"who was the first professor\nof anthropology at Oxford,"},{"time":148435,"text":"one of the first modern anthropologists."},{"time":150431,"text":"In his book on primitive culture,"},{"time":152665,"text":"he says the heart of religion\nis what he called animism,"},{"time":155685,"text":"that is, the belief in spiritual agency,"},{"time":157403,"text":"belief in spirits."},{"time":159780,"text":"The first problem for that definition"},{"time":161788,"text":"is from a recent novel by Paul Beatty called \"Tuff.\""},{"time":164528,"text":"There's a guy talking to a rabbi."},{"time":165934,"text":"The rabbi says he doesn't believe in God."},{"time":168330,"text":"The guy says, \"You're a rabbi,\nhow can you not believe in God?\""},{"time":170760,"text":"And the reply is, \"It's what's\nso great about being Jewish."},{"time":174151,"text":"You don't have to believe in a God per se,"},{"time":176114,"text":"just in being Jewish.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":178570,"text":"So if this guy is a rabbi, and a Jewish rabbi,"},{"time":181598,"text":"and if you have to believe in\nGod in order to be religious,"},{"time":184790,"text":"then we have the rather counterintuitive conclusion"},{"time":188073,"text":"that since it's possible to be a Jewish rabbi"},{"time":190265,"text":"without believing in God,"},{"time":192154,"text":"Judaism isn't a religion."},{"time":194504,"text":"That seems like a pretty counterintuitive thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197970,"text":"Here's another argument against this view."},{"time":201231,"text":"A friend of mine, an Indian friend of mine,"},{"time":203403,"text":"went to his grandfather when he was very young,"},{"time":205586,"text":"a child, and said to him,"},{"time":206721,"text":"\"I want to talk to you about religion,\""},{"time":208840,"text":"and his grandfather said, \"You're too young."},{"time":210085,"text":"Come back when you're a teenager.\""},{"time":211616,"text":"So he came back when he was a teenager,"},{"time":213459,"text":"and he said to his grandfather,"},{"time":215155,"text":"\"It may be a bit late now"},{"time":216481,"text":"because I've discovered that\nI don't believe in the gods.\""},{"time":220221,"text":"And his grandfather, who was a wise man, said,"},{"time":222248,"text":"\"Oh, so you belong to the atheist branch"},{"time":224432,"text":"of the Hindu tradition.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":227618,"text":"And finally, there's this guy,"},{"time":231320,"text":"who famously doesn't believe in God."},{"time":233776,"text":"His name is the Dalai Lama."},{"time":235594,"text":"He often jokes that he's one\nof the world's leading atheists."},{"time":238242,"text":"But it's true, because the Dalai Lama's religion"},{"time":241186,"text":"does not involve belief in God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243966,"text":"Now you might think this just shows"},{"time":245579,"text":"that I've given you the wrong definition"},{"time":248599,"text":"and that I should come up with some other definition"},{"time":250718,"text":"and test it against these cases"},{"time":252416,"text":"and try and find something that captures"},{"time":254987,"text":"atheistic Judaism, atheistic Hinduism,"},{"time":257913,"text":"and atheistic Buddhism as forms of religiosity,"},{"time":261176,"text":"but I actually think that that's a bad idea,"},{"time":262970,"text":"and the reason I think it's a bad idea"},{"time":265299,"text":"is that I don't think that's how"},{"time":266934,"text":"our concept of religion works."},{"time":268565,"text":"I think the way our concept of religion works"},{"time":270165,"text":"is that we actually have, we have a list"},{"time":273203,"text":"of paradigm religions"},{"time":275129,"text":"and their sub-parts, right,"},{"time":278368,"text":"and if something new comes along"},{"time":280922,"text":"that purports to be a religion,"},{"time":282428,"text":"what we ask is, \"Well, is it like one of these?\""},{"time":284892,"text":"Right?"},{"time":287144,"text":"And I think that's not only\nhow we think about religion,"},{"time":289719,"text":"and that's, as it were,"},{"time":291019,"text":"so from our point of view,"},{"time":292810,"text":"anything on that list had better be a religion,"},{"time":294893,"text":"which is why I don't think an account of religion"},{"time":296661,"text":"that excludes Buddhism and Judaism"},{"time":298516,"text":"has a chance of being a good starter,"},{"time":301216,"text":"because they're on our list."},{"time":303920,"text":"But why do we have such a list?"},{"time":305900,"text":"What's going on? How did it come about"},{"time":307730,"text":"that we have this list?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309917,"text":"I think the answer is a pretty simple one"},{"time":312832,"text":"and therefore crude and contentious."},{"time":315960,"text":"I'm sure a lot of people will disagree with it,"},{"time":317349,"text":"but here's my story,"},{"time":318943,"text":"and true or not, it's a story that I think"},{"time":321314,"text":"gives you a good sense of how"},{"time":323742,"text":"the list might have come about,"},{"time":325431,"text":"and therefore helps you to think about"},{"time":326740,"text":"what use the list might be."},{"time":328184,"text":"I think the answer is, European travelers,"},{"time":331472,"text":"starting roughly about the time of Columbus,"},{"time":333305,"text":"started going around the world."},{"time":334930,"text":"They came from a Christian culture,"},{"time":337210,"text":"and when they arrived in a new place,"},{"time":339020,"text":"they noticed that some people\ndidn't have Christianity,"},{"time":341905,"text":"and so they asked themselves\nthe following question:"},{"time":343950,"text":"what have they got instead of Christianity?"},{"time":347140,"text":"And that list was essentially constructed."},{"time":350503,"text":"It consists of the things that other people had"},{"time":352779,"text":"instead of Christianity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355370,"text":"Now there's a difficulty with proceeding in that way,"},{"time":358738,"text":"which is that Christianity is extremely,"},{"time":361178,"text":"even on that list, it's an extremely specific tradition."},{"time":365590,"text":"It has all kinds of things in it"},{"time":367151,"text":"that are very, very particular"},{"time":369277,"text":"that are the results of the specifics"},{"time":371573,"text":"of Christian history,"},{"time":374260,"text":"and one thing that's at the heart of it,"},{"time":375857,"text":"one thing that's at the heart of\nmost understandings of Christianity,"},{"time":378660,"text":"which is the result of the\nspecific history of Christianity,"},{"time":380990,"text":"is that it's an extremely creedal religion."},{"time":384133,"text":"It's a religion in which people are really concerned"},{"time":386813,"text":"about whether you believe the right things."},{"time":389552,"text":"The history of Christianity, the\ninternal history of Christianity,"},{"time":391808,"text":"is largely the history of people killing each other"},{"time":393684,"text":"because they believed the wrong thing,"},{"time":395800,"text":"and it's also involved in"},{"time":397879,"text":"struggles with other religions,"},{"time":399631,"text":"obviously starting in the Middle Ages,"},{"time":403230,"text":"a struggle with Islam,"},{"time":404620,"text":"in which, again, it was the infidelity,"},{"time":407740,"text":"the fact that they didn't believe the right things,"},{"time":409770,"text":"that seemed so offensive to the Christian world."},{"time":413150,"text":"Now that's a very specific and particular history"},{"time":415788,"text":"that Christianity has,"},{"time":418153,"text":"and not everywhere is everything"},{"time":421371,"text":"that has ever been put on this sort of list like it."},{"time":425365,"text":"Here's another problem, I think."},{"time":426772,"text":"A very specific thing happened."},{"time":428110,"text":"It was actually adverted to earlier,"},{"time":429562,"text":"but a very specific thing happened"},{"time":431103,"text":"in the history of the kind of Christianity"},{"time":433292,"text":"that we see around us"},{"time":434813,"text":"mostly in the United States today,"},{"time":436997,"text":"and it happened in the late 19th century,"},{"time":440100,"text":"and that specific thing that happened"},{"time":441509,"text":"in the late 19th century"},{"time":442518,"text":"was a kind of deal that was cut"},{"time":445473,"text":"between science,"},{"time":447983,"text":"this new way of organizing intellectual authority,"},{"time":453676,"text":"and religion."},{"time":454873,"text":"If you think about the 18th century, say,"},{"time":456764,"text":"if you think about intellectual life"},{"time":458234,"text":"before the late 19th century,"},{"time":460590,"text":"anything you did, anything you thought about,"},{"time":463760,"text":"whether it was the physical world,"},{"time":466490,"text":"the human world,"},{"time":468021,"text":"the natural world apart from the human world,"},{"time":470251,"text":"or morality, anything you did"},{"time":472218,"text":"would have been framed against the background"},{"time":473894,"text":"of a set of assumptions that were religious,"},{"time":476357,"text":"Christian assumptions."},{"time":477560,"text":"You couldn't give an account"},{"time":479226,"text":"of the natural world"},{"time":480822,"text":"that didn't say something about its relationship,"},{"time":483744,"text":"for example, to the creation story"},{"time":485552,"text":"in the Abrahamic tradition,"},{"time":487092,"text":"the creation story in the first book of the Torah."},{"time":490296,"text":"So everything was framed in that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493613,"text":"But this changes in the late 19th century,"},{"time":496045,"text":"and for the first time, it's possible for people"},{"time":498370,"text":"to develop serious intellectual careers"},{"time":500749,"text":"as natural historians like Darwin."},{"time":502943,"text":"Darwin worried about the relationship between"},{"time":504928,"text":"what he said and the truths of religion,"},{"time":507481,"text":"but he could proceed, he could write books"},{"time":509406,"text":"about his subject"},{"time":511190,"text":"without having to say what the relationship was"},{"time":513886,"text":"to the religious claims,"},{"time":515358,"text":"and similarly, geologists\nincreasingly could talk about it."},{"time":517740,"text":"In the early 19th century, if you were a geologist"},{"time":519542,"text":"and made a claim about the age of the Earth,"},{"time":521465,"text":"you had to explain whether that was consistent"},{"time":523107,"text":"or how it was or wasn't consistent"},{"time":524537,"text":"with the age of the Earth implied"},{"time":525909,"text":"by the account in Genesis."},{"time":527462,"text":"By the end of the 19th century,"},{"time":528647,"text":"you can just write a geology textbook"},{"time":530160,"text":"in which you make arguments\nabout how old the Earth is."},{"time":532519,"text":"So there's a big change, and that division,"},{"time":534610,"text":"that intellectual division of\nlabor occurs as I say, I think,"},{"time":537545,"text":"and it sort of solidifies so that by the end"},{"time":540370,"text":"of the 19th century in Europe,"},{"time":543528,"text":"there's a real intellectual division of labor,"},{"time":545519,"text":"and you can do all sorts of serious things,"},{"time":547519,"text":"including, increasingly, even philosophy,"},{"time":551421,"text":"without being constrained by the thought,"},{"time":554279,"text":"\"Well, what I have to say has to be consistent"},{"time":556560,"text":"with the deep truths that are given to me"},{"time":559239,"text":"by our religious tradition.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":561749,"text":"So imagine someone who's coming out"},{"time":563913,"text":"of that world, that late-19th-century world,"},{"time":567730,"text":"coming into the country that I grew up in, Ghana,"},{"time":571482,"text":"the society that I grew up in, Asante,"},{"time":573742,"text":"coming into that world"},{"time":575148,"text":"at the turn of the 20th century"},{"time":577164,"text":"with this question that made the list:"},{"time":579187,"text":"what have they got instead of Christianity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":582950,"text":"Well, here's one thing he would have noticed,"},{"time":585807,"text":"and by the way, there was a \nperson who actually did this."},{"time":588151,"text":"His name was Captain Rattray,"},{"time":589450,"text":"he was sent as the British\ngovernment anthropologist,"},{"time":591502,"text":"and he wrote a book about Asante religion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593495,"text":"This is a soul disc."},{"time":596035,"text":"There are many of them in the British Museum."},{"time":598308,"text":"I could give you an interesting, different history"},{"time":599578,"text":"of how it comes about that many of the things"},{"time":601743,"text":"from my society ended up in the British Museum,"},{"time":605134,"text":"but we don't have time for that."},{"time":606945,"text":"So this object is a soul disc."},{"time":608437,"text":"What is a soul disc?"},{"time":609575,"text":"It was worn around the necks"},{"time":611404,"text":"of the soul-washers of the Asante king."},{"time":613974,"text":"What was their job? To wash the king's soul."},{"time":617529,"text":"It would take a long while"},{"time":619434,"text":"to explain how a soul could be the kind of thing"},{"time":621661,"text":"that could be washed,"},{"time":622961,"text":"but Rattray knew that this was religion"},{"time":625740,"text":"because souls were in play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629243,"text":"And similarly,"},{"time":630989,"text":"there were many other things, many other practices."},{"time":633196,"text":"For example, every time anybody\nhad a drink, more or less,"},{"time":635559,"text":"they poured a little bit on the ground"},{"time":637581,"text":"in what's called the libation,"},{"time":639310,"text":"and they gave some to the ancestors."},{"time":640999,"text":"My father did this. Every time\nhe opened a bottle of whiskey,"},{"time":643348,"text":"which I'm glad to say was very often,"},{"time":644869,"text":"he would take the top off and\npour off just a little on the ground,"},{"time":648748,"text":"and he would talk to,"},{"time":650099,"text":"he would say to Akroma-Ampim, the founder of our line,"},{"time":653639,"text":"or Yao Antony, my great uncle,"},{"time":655235,"text":"he would talk to them,"},{"time":657130,"text":"offer them a little bit of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659353,"text":"And finally, there were these\nhuge public ceremonials."},{"time":662238,"text":"This is an early-19th-century drawing"},{"time":663654,"text":"by another British military officer"},{"time":664927,"text":"of such a ceremonial,"},{"time":666977,"text":"where the king was involved,"},{"time":669105,"text":"and the king's job,"},{"time":670511,"text":"one of the large parts of his job,"},{"time":671700,"text":"apart from organizing warfare and things like that,"},{"time":674651,"text":"was to look after the tombs of his ancestors,"},{"time":677997,"text":"and when a king died,"},{"time":679994,"text":"the stool that he sat on was blackened"},{"time":681508,"text":"and put in the royal ancestral temple,"},{"time":684392,"text":"and every 40 days,"},{"time":686521,"text":"the King of Asante has to go and do cult"},{"time":688376,"text":"for his ancestors."},{"time":689738,"text":"That's a large part of his job,"},{"time":691240,"text":"and people think that if he doesn't do it,"},{"time":693113,"text":"things will fall apart."},{"time":694844,"text":"So he's a religious figure,"},{"time":697210,"text":"as Rattray would have said,"},{"time":698535,"text":"as well as a political figure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701160,"text":"So all this would count as religion for Rattray,"},{"time":705844,"text":"but my point is that when you look"},{"time":707783,"text":"into the lives of those people,"},{"time":709165,"text":"you also find that every time they do anything,"},{"time":711910,"text":"they're conscious of the ancestors."},{"time":713944,"text":"Every morning at breakfast,"},{"time":715977,"text":"you can go outside the front of the house"},{"time":717803,"text":"and make an offering to the god tree, the nyame dua"},{"time":720899,"text":"outside your house,"},{"time":722083,"text":"and again, you'll talk to the gods"},{"time":723400,"text":"and the high gods and the low gods"},{"time":724426,"text":"and the ancestors and so on."},{"time":726084,"text":"This is not a world"},{"time":727620,"text":"in which the separation between religion and science"},{"time":730527,"text":"has occurred."},{"time":732101,"text":"Religion has not being separated"},{"time":733644,"text":"from any other areas of life,"},{"time":734920,"text":"and in particular,"},{"time":736917,"text":"what's crucial to understand about this world"},{"time":738612,"text":"is that it's a world in which the job"},{"time":740150,"text":"that science does for us"},{"time":741288,"text":"is done by what Rattray is going to call religion,"},{"time":744432,"text":"because if they want an explanation of something,"},{"time":746372,"text":"if they want to know why the crop just failed,"},{"time":748200,"text":"if they want to know why it's raining"},{"time":749486,"text":"or not raining, if they need rain,"},{"time":751904,"text":"if they want to know why"},{"time":754428,"text":"their grandfather has died,"},{"time":756287,"text":"they are going to appeal to the very same entities,"},{"time":759195,"text":"the very same language,"},{"time":760637,"text":"talk to the very same gods about that."},{"time":763253,"text":"This great separation, in other words,"},{"time":765342,"text":"between religion and science hasn't happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767273,"text":"Now, this would be a mere historical curiosity,"},{"time":771598,"text":"except that in large parts of the world,"},{"time":775050,"text":"this is still the truth."},{"time":777794,"text":"I had the privilege of going to a wedding"},{"time":779802,"text":"the other day in northern Namibia,"},{"time":781567,"text":"20 miles or so south of the Angolan border"},{"time":784412,"text":"in a village of 200 people."},{"time":786145,"text":"These were modern people."},{"time":787313,"text":"We had with us Oona Chaplin,"},{"time":789204,"text":"who some of you may have heard of,"},{"time":790613,"text":"and one of the people from\nthis village came up to her,"},{"time":792692,"text":"and said, \"I've seen you in 'Game of Thrones.'\""},{"time":795423,"text":"So these were not people who\nwere isolated from our world,"},{"time":799251,"text":"but nevertheless, for them,"},{"time":800780,"text":"the gods and the spirits are still very much there,"},{"time":803333,"text":"and when we were on the bus going back and forth"},{"time":805159,"text":"to the various parts of the [ceremony],"},{"time":806821,"text":"they prayed not just in a generic way"},{"time":809398,"text":"but for the safety of the journey,"},{"time":810859,"text":"and they meant it,"},{"time":811770,"text":"and when they said to me that my mother,"},{"time":814932,"text":"the bridegroom's [grandmother],"},{"time":816623,"text":"was with us, they didn't mean it figuratively."},{"time":819185,"text":"They meant, even though she was a dead person,"},{"time":821940,"text":"they meant that she was still around."},{"time":824518,"text":"So in large parts of the world today,"},{"time":827067,"text":"that separation between science and religion"},{"time":829229,"text":"hasn't occurred in large parts of the world today,"},{"time":830910,"text":"and as I say, these are not --"},{"time":834638,"text":"This guy used to work for Chase and at the World Bank."},{"time":839440,"text":"These are fellow citizens of the world with you,"},{"time":842147,"text":"but they come from a place in which religion"},{"time":843956,"text":"is occupying a very different role."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845867,"text":"So what I want you to think about\nnext time somebody wants"},{"time":847993,"text":"to make some vast generalization about religion"},{"time":850473,"text":"is that maybe there isn't such a thing"},{"time":853214,"text":"as a religion, such a thing as religion,"},{"time":855845,"text":"and that therefore what they say"},{"time":857501,"text":"cannot possibly be true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860314,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}